      "message": "\u003e I wasn\u0027t sure which one was correct.  I think it\u0027s identifier_info.thread_id; and not MachThreadSelf(), or are they the same?\n\nThey’re the same. But one calls just into the kernel, and the other does some user-space stuff to get the same value already cached in user space. The question is, “is the user-space version provably safe?” Is it on Rohit’s list?",
