      "writtenOn": "2020-03-19T21:04:51Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e Changed to \u0027int32_t\u0027 (not sure when to use int32_t vs int...)\n\nsiginfo_t::si_code is an int.\n\nI almost never have a use for int32_t.\n\nSomething’s an $type when another interface you’re using says it is. Keep types correct and consistent, until you have a need to change to another type (at an interface boundary, for example). And when that happens, be careful about the conversion. If the original value might not fit cleanly into the new type, do your own range check (we have helpers for this) or use an appropriate cast, like checked_cast or saturated_cast.",
      "parentUuid": "11477840_d9a7eb50",
